response.question: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n). This is because, in the worst-case scenario, the algorithm may have to iterate through all 'n' elements in the list to find the target value.
response.feedback: The student's answer is correct. The time complexity of a linear search algorithm is O(n), as in the worst case, every element in the list needs to be checked.
